            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“For the first time anywhere, an insurance regulator will have the mandate to push insurers to bring their investments and underwriting in line with science-based emissions reduction targets. Insurance company investments and underwriting keep allowing the expansion of fossil fuel infrastructure that fuels global warming, putting insurance markets and consumers at risk,” said Yevgeny Shrago, Policy Counsel at Public Citizen’s Climate Program, in a statement about new Connecticut legislation to tackle the role of insurers in fossil fuel financing.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
